# API route conventions

## Handler template

Every route handler follows this order:

```ts
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";
import { featureGuard } from "@/lib/features";
import { checkRateLimit, createRateLimitResponse } from "@/lib/rate-limit";
import { createServerClient } from "@supabase/ssr";
import { cookies } from "next/headers";
import { SomeSchema } from "@/lib/validations/schemas";

export async function POST(request: Request) {
  // 1. Feature flag (if the route is flagged)
  const guard = featureGuard("featureName");
  if (guard) return guard;

  // 2. Rate limit
  const rl = await checkRateLimit(request, "general");
  if (!rl.allowed) return createRateLimitResponse(rl);

  // 3. Auth — server-validated JWT
  const cookieStore = await cookies();
  const supabase = createServerClient(
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!,
    { cookies: { getAll: () => cookieStore.getAll() } }
  );
  const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
  if (!user?.id) {
    return NextResponse.json(
      { error: "Authentication required", code: "UNAUTHORIZED" },
      { status: 401 }
    );
  }

  // 4. Parse + validate
  const body = await request.json();
  const parsed = SomeSchema.safeParse(body);
  if (!parsed.success) {
    return NextResponse.json(
      { error: "Invalid input", code: "VALIDATION_ERROR", details: parsed.error.flatten() },
      { status: 400 }
    );
  }

  // 5. Logic…

  return NextResponse.json({ success: true, data: /* ... */ });
}
```

## Response shape

- Success: `{ success: true, data?: ... }`
- Error: `{ error: string, code: string, message?: string, details?: any }` with an appropriate HTTP status (400/401/403/404/409/422/429/500).

## Admin routes

- Use `checkIsAdmin(userId)` from `@/lib/supabase/auth` after verifying `user` from `supabase.auth.getUser()`. Return 403 with `code: "FORBIDDEN"` on failure.
- Admin routes under `app/api/admin/` may also accept `Authorization: Bearer ${CRON_SECRET}` for automation — see `app/api/admin/route.ts::checkAdminAuth` as the reference.

## Rate-limit buckets

`'general' | 'voting' | 'auth' | 'submission' | 'admin' | 'analytics'` — pick the narrowest that fits the handler.

## Forbidden

- Do not add `console.log`/`info`/`debug`. Use `console.error`/`console.warn` only.
- Do not use `supabase.auth.getSession()` directly in routes — it only reads cookies without validating the JWT server-side. Use `getUser()`.
- Do not bypass RLS by using `getSupabaseAdmin()` when the user's own credentials would suffice. Reserve `getSupabaseAdmin` for operations the user legitimately can't do themselves.
- Do not sanitize user strings by hand — use `sanitizeString` from `@/lib/validations/schemas`.
